{
  "texts": [
    "In this section, we present a categorization of disinformation detection methods, based on the algorithms employed.",
    "Figure 6 illustrates this categorization.",
    "Initially, the methods are classified into two categories based on whether they utilize machine learning techniques or not.",
    "The first category comprises methods that do not employ machine learning algorithms, such as the rhetorical approach, which involves manipulating sentence components to enhance the persuasive impact of speech.",
    "Rhetorical Structure Theory (RST) is a theoretical framework for organizing text that explains the relationships that exist between different parts of a discourse."
  ]
}